{"lemma":"شِيحٌ","slug":"شِيحٌ","root":"ش.#.ح","root_slug":"ش-_-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23468"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wormwood (Artemisia gen. et spp.)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic attested as Classical Syriac ܣܝܺܚܳܐ (sīḥā) and ܫܝܺܚܳܐ (šīḥā, “Artemisia judaica”), as well as in Hebrew שִׂיחַ (síakh, “Artemisia judaica; shoot, shrub”) and in Akkadian 𒋛𒄿𒈝 (sīḫum, “wormwood”). Perhaps related to the root ش ي ع (š y ʕ), meaning “to spread”, “to sprout out”, “to come forth”; compare شَيْعَة (šayʕa, “bush, short tree”)."},"ipa":["/ʃiːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23468","headword_ar":"شِيحٌ","root":"$yH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cautious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fearing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAy^iHN","text_ar":"شَايِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$iyHN","text_ar":"مُشِيحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, O:) or this last,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cautious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fearing, and at the same time striving, labouring, toiling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerting himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) or all signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prudent; discreet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"using, precaution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good judgment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 281;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoHaAnu","text_ar":"شَيْحَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Id. p. 43.) ―         -b2-  In the dial. of Hudheyl, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Striving, labouring, toiling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerting himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K,) in affairs; (S, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAy^iHN","text_ar":"شَايِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$iyHN","text_ar":"مُشِيحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, O, K:) pl. of the first [and app. of the second also]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyaAHN","text_ar":"شِيَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O.)       -A2-  Also [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"artemisia Judaïca;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absinthium Ponticum; species of wormwood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, S, A, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of several species,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of some"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereof brooms are made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which is also used for fumigation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves of which are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadab","text_ar":"هَدَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHn, O, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it has a sweet odour, but its taste is bitter; is pasture for horses and camels; and the places of its growth are the plains and the meadows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O, L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyHaAnN","text_ar":"شِيحَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, O, L.)       -A3-  Accord. to the K, [probably on the authority of Lth,] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Yemen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that there is no kind of garment so called: the correct word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayoHN","text_ar":"سَيْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with [the unpointed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and with fet-h]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","TA","As","O","Az","S","K","AHn","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}